---
description: Policy precedence and conflict resolution
alwaysApply: true
---

When instructions conflict, apply this precedence order (highest wins):

1. user instruction for this session
2. system/environment constraints
3. repository `alwaysApply` rules
4. task-specific applied rules
5. command playbooks
6. agent-local guidance

If two rules at the same precedence conflict, follow the stricter safety constraint and report the conflict in the final summary.

If a command playbook conflicts with policy at higher precedence, rewrite command execution to remain compliant instead of skipping policy.
